Class CommandArgumentList

    public class CommandArgumentList
extends java.util.AbstractList<CommandArgument>
implements java.util.RandomAccess
    A list implementation for CommandArguments that includes a specialized iterator. All arguments are in lowercase.

      • indexOfType

        public int indexOfType(int startIndex,
                       java.lang.Class<?> type)
        Finds the first argument of the specified type that occurs after the index given.
        Parameters:
        startIndex - The index from which to start searching.
        type - The ArgumentTypeMapper to search for.
        Returns:
        The index of the argument if found. If none of the arguments match the type provided, -1 is returned. If the startIndex provided is less than 0, it will be treated as 0. If the startIndex provided is greater than or equal to the size of this list, -1 will be returned.
